This paper discusses a smartphone authentication method that focuses on human behavioral activity cycles. It involves analyzing data from sensors on the smartphone, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of an algorithm to analyze this data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the security implications of this authentication method, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves data analysis and modeling, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
